 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT PROPOSAL: S0-CLOSE — Validate Core Hypothesis — Priority 4 (Sessions 49-50). PROBLEM: Stage 0 success criterion ('work 25 turns, harvest, start fresh — new session picks up seamlessly') has not been mechanically validated after 46 sessions. DOGFOOD-2 scored 3.48/10 on external Go CLI project. The foundational hypothesis — harvest/seed transforms workflow — lacks definitive evidence. SOLUTION: Define and execute the S0 success criterion mechanically: (1) Select an external project (non-DDIS, non-Rust). (2) Work 25 turns using braid harvest/seed lifecycle. (3) Harvest and start a completely fresh session with seed only. (4) Measure whether the new session can continue without manual re-explanation. (5) Score rigorously using a rubric (context retention, task continuity, methodology adherence). FIRST-PRINCIPLES JUSTIFICATION: The entire project exists to validate this hypothesis. 46 sessions of infrastructure building without definitive validation is an axiological divergence — the implementation may have drifted from the goal. If harvest/seed works on external data, the architecture is validated and Stages 1-4 are justified. If it fails, we need to diagnose whether the problem is seed assembly quality, harvest extraction quality, or the fundamental concept. VERIFICATION APPROACH: (1) Pre-registered rubric with 10 criteria scored 1-10. (2) Two independent trials on different external projects. (3) Score ≥ 7/10 = validated. Score 5-7 = needs tuning. Score < 5 = fundamental issue. (4) Compare against DOGFOOD-2 baseline (3.48/10). DEPENDENCIES: Benefits from Priority 1 (calibration fix) and Priority 3 (coverage fix) for accurate self-assessment during the trial. Can proceed independently but results will be more meaningful with calibrated measurements. UNBLOCKS: Strategic direction for entire project. If validated: proceed to Stages 1-4. If failed: redirect to fixing harvest/seed before any intelligence work. TRACES TO: SEED.md Stage 0 success criterion, ADR-FOUNDATION-012 (epistemology runtime)."
